title: Names of teens killed in drive-by shooting released
content:
Deputies released the names of the two teenagers killed in a shooting Thursday.
Teryus Garmon, 16, and Lee Nelson, 18, were shot on the 2300 block of Fontainebleau Dr. before 10:45 p.m. Thursday, deputies said.
They were found in a driveway and taken to Florida Hospital, where they were pronounced dead.
Two witnesses, both 15 years old, told deputies they saw a dark-colored, four-door sedan, possibly a Mercedes, going south on Fontainebleau Drive, deputies said.
Someone inside the car started shooting at the house, deputies said.
Deputies have not released a suspect description.
Anyone with more information about the case can call Crimeline at 1-800-423-8477.
